 <p>Tea preparation is the process of turning tea leaves into a beverage.While the particular steps vary with the type of tea and with the raw materials,the process includes fourbasic steps;raw tea leaves must be<a href="grinding.html"> ground </a>the ground tea leaves must then be mixed with hot water for a certain time (<a href="brewing.html">brewed</a>),and finally the liquid tea must be seperated from the used grounds.</p>
 
<p>During the 17th century, drinking tea became fashionable among the English, who started to plant tea on a large scale in British India.The term herbal tea refers to drinks not made from Camellia sinensis. They are the infusions of fruit, leaves, or other plant parts, such as steeps of rosehip, chamomile, or rooibos. These may be called tisanes or herbal infusions to prevent confusion with tea made from the tea plant.</p>

<p>To learn more about tea,just browse our information site,or you can visit http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tea_preparation wikipedia for even more.</p>
